IterableStitcher<T> - Class in goal.util
An Iterable that will 'stitch' an iteration of iterations.

Using yield return as an indicator what the next() method of the IterableStitcher.iterator() should return, the following pseudo-code describes the working of this class:

  for (Iterable<? extends T> subIter : allIters)
    for (T value : subIter)
      yield return value;

ModuleCallAction - Class in goal.core.program.actions
Action that makes the agent focus on a module, using one of four methods; When the action is executed, and the agent focuses on the module, the new attention set will consist of one goal, which validates the entire context of the Module.
To use this method, focus on a Module with the Module.FocusMethod.SELECT focus method.

Note that this method has better performance, as no new databases need to be created due to the context.

Validator for Modules.
Checks for the following errors: Goals in the goals section with free variables that are not instantiated by the module's parameters.
